<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
BOLIVIA. Tarija, Prov. Aniceto Arce Ruiz, La Merced, 30 km de Padcaya hacia Bermejo, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S.G. Beck, R. Kiesling &amp; D. Metzing</emphasis>
22139 (holotype LPB, isotypes SI n.v., K [leaves only]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Stout trailing or weakly ascending plant; stems lanate. Leaves petiolate, 7-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-10 cm, ovate, base cordate with rounded overlapping auricles, apex acute, adaxially appressed white-villous, abaxially densely white lanate-tomentose; petiole 3-6 cm. Flowers 1(-3) in pedunculate, axillary cymes; peduncles 5-7 cm, lanate, straight or nearly so; bracteoles 2-3 mm, lanceolate, somewhat persistent; pedicels 8 mm; sepals subequal, 15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, oblong-lanceolate to oblong-ovate, obtuse, lanate; corolla 7-8 cm long, funnel-shaped, uniformly pink, tomentose at base and on midpetaline bands, limb c. 5 cm diam. Capsules and seeds not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
